## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [ring1a/ring1b]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Plieotrophic defects. Leaves may be lobed, downward curving or make ectopic meristems. The SAM is enlarged and phyllotaxy is abnormal and the shoot apex may terminate in a cluster of flowers with extra floral organs.Occasional homeotic conversion of petals to stamens.
   - [ring1a/ring1b/clf-26]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;lants are extremely small with a reduced number of leaves, leaves are sessile and the inflorescences are completely arrested. Cotyledons are relatively well expanded.Enhanced de-repression of KNOX gene expression.
   - [ring1a/ring1b/tfl2-2]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Plants are extremely small with a reduced number of leaves, leaves are sessile and the inflorescences are completely arrested.Enhanced de-repression of KNOX gene expression.
